Visitor Management System (VMS)
This project is a complete visitor management system with a web portal for administrators and guards, and a mobile application for guards.

Project Structure
This repository contains three main sub-projects:

/vms-backend: The Node.js, Express, and PostgreSQL backend API.

/vms-frontend: The React web application for admins and guards.

/vmsmobile: The React Native (Expo) mobile application for guards.

Getting Started
1. Start the Database

The database runs in a Docker container. Make sure you have Docker Desktop installed and running.

# From the root 'vms' directory
docker-compose up -d

2. Run the Backend Server

Navigate into the backend folder, install dependencies, and start the server.

cd vms-backend
npm install
npm run dev

The backend will be running at http://localhost:8080.

3. Run the Frontend Web App

In a new terminal, navigate into the frontend folder, install dependencies, and start the server.

cd vms-frontend
npm install
npm run dev

The web app will be accessible at http://localhost:5173.

4. Run the Mobile App

In another new terminal, navigate into the mobile folder, install dependencies, and start the server.

cd vmsmobile
npm install
npx expo start

Scan the QR code with the Expo Go app on your phone to run the mobile app.

